Class SublistManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • docreader.list.SublistManager

  • final class SublistManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Determines the fully qualified identifier for a list-item and takes care about correct parent/child-relationships
    Author:
    Moritz Dorka

      • processParagraph

        SublistManager.LevelTupleWFakeNumberText processParagraph(long lsid,
                                                          int ilvl,
                                                          java.lang.String numberText)
        Process some text (usually a heading) which does not fit to any list pattern but we need to squeeze it in there, nevertheless.

        This is similar to a fakeList paragraph (see fakeListManager) but we do not have any usable olvl and indent information available.

        Parameters:
        lsid - lsid of the paragraph to be inserted
        ilvl - level at which this paragraph should be inserted
        numberText - (fake) numberText of the paragraph
        Returns:
        wrapper class which contains a LevelTuple representing this new paragraph and a numberText; none of which may be null

      • getLevelDifference

        int getLevelDifference()
        Compute the hierarchical difference between the current level and its predecessor;
        must be called after prependFullyQualified(docreader.list.SublistManager.LevelStore.LevelTuple)

        Note: If there are placeholder elements (skipped levels) "current level" refers to the level of the very first placeholder element.

        Returns:
        <0
        current is child of some more significant level than that of the predecessor
        0
        both items are on the same level
        >0
        current is child of predecessor
